# LearnHub Module Structure

LearnHub follows a modular architecture with separate modules for different concerns:

## Module Organization
Each module follows a similar structure with domain models, services, and mappers:

- **learnhub-api**: Main API controllers and application entry point
  - [Controllers](mdc:learnhub-api/learnhub-api/src/main/java/xyz/learnhub/api/controller) - API endpoints
  - [Request DTOs](mdc:learnhub-api/learnhub-api/src/main/java/xyz/learnhub/api/request) - Request data objects
  - [Configuration](mdc:learnhub-api/learnhub-api/src/main/java/xyz/learnhub/api/config) - Module-specific configuration

- **learnhub-common**: Shared utilities, base classes, and common functionality
  - [Constants](mdc:learnhub-api/learnhub-common/src/main/java/xyz/learnhub/common/constant) - System constants
  - [Exceptions](mdc:learnhub-api/learnhub-common/src/main/java/xyz/learnhub/common/exception) - Custom exceptions
  - [Utilities](mdc:learnhub-api/learnhub-common/src/main/java/xyz/learnhub/common/util) - Common utility classes
  - [Base Models](mdc:learnhub-api/learnhub-common/src/main/java/xyz/learnhub/common/bus) - Base model classes

- **learnhub-resource**: Resource management (files, media, etc.)
  - [Domain Models](mdc:learnhub-api/learnhub-resource/src/main/java/xyz/learnhub/resource/domain) - Entity classes
  - [Services](mdc:learnhub-api/learnhub-resource/src/main/java/xyz/learnhub/resource/service) - Business logic
  - [Mappers](mdc:learnhub-api/learnhub-resource/src/main/java/xyz/learnhub/resource/mapper) - Database access layer

- **learnhub-course**: Course management functionality
  - [Domain Models](mdc:learnhub-api/learnhub-course/src/main/java/xyz/learnhub/course/domain) - Course entities
  - [Services](mdc:learnhub-api/learnhub-course/src/main/java/xyz/learnhub/course/service) - Course business logic
  - [Mappers](mdc:learnhub-api/learnhub-course/src/main/java/xyz/learnhub/course/mapper) - Course data access

- **learnhub-system**: System administration functionality
  - [Domain Models](mdc:learnhub-api/learnhub-system/src/main/java/xyz/learnhub/system/domain) - System entities
  - [Services](mdc:learnhub-api/learnhub-system/src/main/java/xyz/learnhub/system/service) - System business logic
  - [Mappers](mdc:learnhub-api/learnhub-system/src/main/java/xyz/learnhub/system/mapper) - System data access

## Domain-Driven Design
The codebase follows a layered architecture with:
- Controllers: Handle API requests and responses
- Services: Implement business logic
- Mappers: Data access layer (using MyBatis)
- Domain models: Entity classes representing business objects

This modular approach allows for separation of concerns and easier maintainability.
